            <title>[WFLY-1699] On Windows, html files are locked after being accessed in browser</title>
                <link>https://issues.jboss.org/browse/WFLY-1699</link>
                <project id="12313721" key="WFLY">WildFly</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;On windows, if you deploy a web project with Eclipse/JBossTools/JBDS, once an html file has been accessed with a browser, the file is locked (by the wildfly java process). This prevents incremental deployment (change file + save + publish). See &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.jboss.org/browse/JBIDE-15203&quot; title=&quot;Error publishing html files to WildFly on Windows (WildFly locks deployed files)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JBIDE-15203&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;JBIDE-15203&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

